## Risks

High: this is the largest UI slice — the `Commands.fs` registry must be the
single source from which both the key map and the mouse map derive (AC‑E1 is
the constraint‑0.4 lynchpin), and `ConstructorView.fs` wires every gesture
through it without a second binding site. The headless simulation of
wheel/drag gestures in `OpticalConstructor.Ui.Tests` is the main test
care‑point. Keep the MVU model pure and serializable (0.3).

## Hand-off

Record the `Commands.fs` registry shape (the command DU, the three‑state
binding type, how the key map and mouse map are projected) so slice 006
(Ribbon) projects ribbon + menu controls from the *same* registry with no
second wiring site, and so slice 007 (Part G) adds the group‑toggle and
detector `Set as primary` commands in this one place. Record the
`ConstructorView` MVU model/msg surface so slices 006 (catalogue drag‑in,
value‑id modal) and 007 (group on/off, K snapshot push) extend it. Note that
every project‑mutating action this slice dispatches MUST be wired to push an
`EditHistory` snapshot in slice 007 (Part K). Carry the `gates:` baseline
YAML block forward.
